The Foundational Oath
Every Trustee, upon assuming office, must take this public oath:

"I acknowledge that these robotic assets are 'Makkal Sotthu' (Public Wealth), not mine to own or exploit. I swear that I shall serve as a humble custodian, ensuring these machines provide for the collective well-being without exception. I pledge never to accept a bribe, never to divert resources for personal or partisan gain, and I submit myself to the constant oversight of the people I serve. If I fail this trust, I forfeit my position and my stewardship instantly."

The "Single Most Important Rule"
To ensure this oath isn't just words, the document must contain one non-negotiable rule that governs the Trustee's entire tenure:

"The Principle of Total Transparency and Reciprocity:"

"Every action, movement, and deployment of the robotic infrastructure must be recorded on a public, immutable ledger, accessible in real-time to every citizen. The Trustee holds authority only so long as the infrastructure serves the public need; the moment the service deviates from the common good, any citizen—as an Active Auditor—holds the immediate right to trigger a 'Systemic Pause' and demand a public inquiry."
